-- East Africa Portland Climbs as Kenyan Government Starts Selling Its Shares
-- Eric Ombok
-- 2010-06-16T08:56:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/east-africa-portland-climbs-as-kenyan-government-starts-selling-its-shares.html

          
          
             East Africa Portland Cement Co. ,
Kenya’s second-largest cement maker, headed for its highest
closing level this month after the government said it started
the process of selling shares in the company.  
 The shares rose 4 shillings, or 3.3 percent, to 124
shillings at 11:30 a.m. in Nairobi.  
 Kenya’s  government has shortlisted nine consortia to
provide advisory services for the share sale, Nairobi-based
Business Daily said today, citing Solomon Kitungu, chief
executive officer of the Privatization Commission.  
 The government owns has a direct shareholding of 25.3
percent in the company and a further 27 percent through the
state-controlled National Social Security Fund, Business Daily
said.  
